199enum ArrayBufferViewSubtag {
200 DataViewTag = 0,
201 Int8ArrayTag = 1,
202 Uint8ArrayTag = 2,
203 Uint8ClampedArrayTag = 3,
204 Int16ArrayTag = 4,
205 Uint16ArrayTag = 5,
206 Int32ArrayTag = 6,
207 Uint32ArrayTag = 7,
208 Float32ArrayTag = 8,
209 Float64ArrayTag = 9,
210 BigInt64ArrayTag = 10,
211 BigUint64ArrayTag = 11,
212};
213
214static unsigned typedArrayElementSize(ArrayBufferViewSubtag tag)
215{
216 switch (tag) {
217 case DataViewTag:
218 case Int8ArrayTag:
219 case Uint8ArrayTag:
220 case Uint8ClampedArrayTag:
221 return 1;
222 case Int16ArrayTag:
223 case Uint16ArrayTag:
224 return 2;
225 case Int32ArrayTag:
226 case Uint32ArrayTag:
227 case Float32ArrayTag:
228 return 4;
229 case Float64ArrayTag:
230 case BigInt64ArrayTag:
231 case BigUint64ArrayTag:
232 return 8;
233 default:
234 return 0;
235 }
236}

299static unsigned countUsages(CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages)
300{
301 // Fast bit count algorithm for sparse bit maps.
302 unsigned count = 0;
303 while (usages) {
304 usages = usages & (usages - 1);
305 ++count;
306 }
307 return count;
308}

312/* CurrentVersion tracks the serialization version so that persistent stores
313 * are able to correctly bail out in the case of encountering newer formats.
314 *
315 * Initial version was 1.
316 * Version 2. added the ObjectReferenceTag and support for serialization of cyclic graphs.
317 * Version 3. added the FalseObjectTag, TrueObjectTag, NumberObjectTag, StringObjectTag
318 * and EmptyStringObjectTag for serialization of Boolean, Number and String objects.
319 * Version 4. added support for serializing non-index properties of arrays.
320 * Version 5. added support for Map and Set types.
321 * Version 6. added support for 8-bit strings.
322 * Version 7. added support for File's lastModified attribute.
323 * Version 8. added support for ImageData's colorSpace attribute.
324 */
325static const unsigned CurrentVersion = 8;
326static const unsigned TerminatorTag = 0xFFFFFFFF;
327static const unsigned StringPoolTag = 0xFFFFFFFE;
328static const unsigned NonIndexPropertiesTag = 0xFFFFFFFD;
329
330// The high bit of a StringData's length determines the character size.
331static const unsigned StringDataIs8BitFlag = 0x80000000;
332
333/*
334 * Object serialization is performed according to the following grammar, all tags
335 * are recorded as a single uint8_t.
336 *
337 * IndexType (used for the object pool and StringData's constant pool) is the
338 * minimum sized unsigned integer type required to represent the maximum index
339 * in the constant pool.
340 *
341 * SerializedValue :- <CurrentVersion:uint32_t> Value
342 * Value :- Array | Object | Map | Set | Terminal
343 *
344 * Array :-
345 * ArrayTag <length:uint32_t>(<index:uint32_t><value:Value>)* TerminatorTag
346 *
347 * Object :-
348 * ObjectTag (<name:StringData><value:Value>)* TerminatorTag
349 *
350 * Map :- MapObjectTag MapData
351 *
352 * Set :- SetObjectTag SetData
353 *
354 * MapData :- (<key:Value><value:Value>)* NonMapPropertiesTag (<name:StringData><value:Value>)* TerminatorTag
355 * SetData :- (<key:Value>)* NonSetPropertiesTag (<name:StringData><value:Value>)* TerminatorTag
356 *
357 * Terminal :-
358 * UndefinedTag
359 * | NullTag
360 * | IntTag <value:int32_t>
361 * | ZeroTag
362 * | OneTag
363 * | FalseTag
364 * | TrueTag
365 * | FalseObjectTag
366 * | TrueObjectTag
367 * | DoubleTag <value:double>
368 * | NumberObjectTag <value:double>
369 * | DateTag <value:double>
370 * | String
371 * | EmptyStringTag
372 * | EmptyStringObjectTag
373 * | BigInt
374 * | File
375 * | FileList
376 * | ImageData
377 * | Blob
378 * | ObjectReference
379 * | MessagePortReferenceTag <value:uint32_t>
380 * | ArrayBuffer
381 * | ArrayBufferViewTag ArrayBufferViewSubtag <byteOffset:uint32_t> <byteLength:uint32_t> (ArrayBuffer | ObjectReference)
382 * | CryptoKeyTag <wrappedKeyLength:uint32_t> <factor:byte{wrappedKeyLength}>
383 * | DOMPoint
384 * | DOMRect
385 * | DOMMatrix
386 * | DOMQuad
387 * | ImageBitmapTransferTag <value:uint32_t>
388 * | RTCCertificateTag
389 * | ImageBitmapTag <originClean:uint8_t> <logicalWidth:int32_t> <logicalHeight:int32_t> <resolutionScale:double> <byteLength:uint32_t>(<imageByteData:uint8_t>)
390 * | OffscreenCanvasTransferTag <value:uint32_t>
391 * | WasmMemoryTag <value:uint32_t>
392 * | RTCDataChannelTransferTag <processIdentifier:uint64_t><rtcDataChannelIdentifier:uint64_t><label:String>
393 * | DOMExceptionTag <message:String> <name:String>
394 *
395 * Inside certificate, data is serialized in this format as per spec:
396 *
397 * <expires:double> <certificate:StringData> <origin:StringData> <keyingMaterial:StringData>
398 * We also add fingerprints to make sure we expose to JavaScript the same information.
399 *
400 * Inside wrapped crypto key, data is serialized in this format:
401 *
402 * <keyFormatVersion:uint32_t> <extractable:int32_t> <usagesCount:uint32_t> <usages:byte{usagesCount}> CryptoKeyClassSubtag (CryptoKeyHMAC | CryptoKeyAES | CryptoKeyRSA)
403 *
404 * String :-
405 * EmptyStringTag
406 * StringTag StringData
407 *
408 * StringObject:
409 * EmptyStringObjectTag
410 * StringObjectTag StringData
411 *
412 * StringData :-
413 * StringPoolTag <cpIndex:IndexType>
414 * (not (TerminatorTag | StringPoolTag))<is8Bit:uint32_t:1><length:uint32_t:31><characters:CharType{length}> // Added to constant pool when seen, string length 0xFFFFFFFF is disallowed
415 *
416 * BigInt :-
417 * BigIntTag BigIntData
418 * BigIntObjectTag BigIntData
419 *
420 * BigIntData :-
421 * <sign:uint8_t> <lengthInUint64:uint32_t> <contents:uint64_t{lengthInUint64}>
422 *
423 * File :-
424 * FileTag FileData
425 *
426 * FileData :-
427 * <path:StringData> <url:StringData> <type:StringData> <name:StringData> <lastModified:double>
428 *
429 * FileList :-
430 * FileListTag <length:uint32_t>(<file:FileData>){length}
431 *
432 * ImageData :-
433 * ImageDataTag <width:int32_t> <height:int32_t> <length:uint32_t> <data:uint8_t{length}> <colorSpace:PredefinedColorSpaceTag>
434 *
435 * Blob :-
436 * BlobTag <url:StringData><type:StringData><size:long long>
437 *
438 * RegExp :-
439 * RegExpTag <pattern:StringData><flags:StringData>
440 *
441 * ObjectReference :-
442 * ObjectReferenceTag <opIndex:IndexType>
443 *
444 * ArrayBuffer :-
445 * ArrayBufferTag <length:uint32_t> <contents:byte{length}>
446 * ArrayBufferTransferTag <value:uint32_t>
447 * SharedArrayBufferTag <value:uint32_t>
448 *
449 * CryptoKeyHMAC :-
450 * <keySize:uint32_t> <keyData:byte{keySize}> CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag // Algorithm tag inner hash function.
451 *
452 * CryptoKeyAES :-
453 * CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag <keySize:uint32_t> <keyData:byte{keySize}>
454 *
455 * CryptoKeyRSA :-
456 * CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag <isRestrictedToHash:int32_t> CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag? CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag CryptoKeyRSAPublicComponents CryptoKeyRSAPrivateComponents?
457 *
458 * CryptoKeyRSAPublicComponents :-
459 * <modulusSize:uint32_t> <modulus:byte{modulusSize}> <exponentSize:uint32_t> <exponent:byte{exponentSize}>
460 *
461 * CryptoKeyRSAPrivateComponents :-
462 * <privateExponentSize:uint32_t> <privateExponent:byte{privateExponentSize}> <primeCount:uint32_t> FirstPrimeInfo? PrimeInfo{primeCount - 1}
463 *
464 * // CRT data could be computed from prime factors. It is only serialized to reuse a code path that's needed for JWK.
465 * FirstPrimeInfo :-
466 * <factorSize:uint32_t> <factor:byte{factorSize}> <crtExponentSize:uint32_t> <crtExponent:byte{crtExponentSize}>
467 *
468 * PrimeInfo :-
469 * <factorSize:uint32_t> <factor:byte{factorSize}> <crtExponentSize:uint32_t> <crtExponent:byte{crtExponentSize}> <crtCoefficientSize:uint32_t> <crtCoefficient:byte{crtCoefficientSize}>
470 *
471 * CryptoKeyEC :-
472 * CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag <namedCurve:StringData> CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag <keySize:uint32_t> <keyData:byte{keySize}>
473 *
474 * CryptoKeyRaw :-
475 * CryptoAlgorithmIdentifierTag <keySize:uint32_t> <keyData:byte{keySize}>
476 *
477 * DOMPoint :-
478 * DOMPointReadOnlyTag DOMPointData
479 * | DOMPointTag DOMPointData
480 *
481 * DOMPointData :-
482 * <x:double> <y:double> <z:double> <w:double>
483 *
484 * DOMRect :-
485 * DOMRectReadOnlyTag DOMRectData
486 * | DOMRectTag DOMRectData
487 *
488 * DOMRectData :-
489 * <x:double> <y:double> <width:double> <height:double>
490 *
491 * DOMMatrix :-
492 * DOMMatrixReadOnlyTag DOMMatrixData
493 * | DOMMatrixTag DOMMatrixData
494 *
495 * DOMMatrixData :-
496 * <is2D:uint8_t:true> <m11:double> <m12:double> <m21:double> <m22:double> <m41:double> <m42:double>
497 * | <is2D:uint8_t:false> <m11:double> <m12:double> <m13:double> <m14:double> <m21:double> <m22:double> <m23:double> <m24:double> <m31:double> <m32:double> <m33:double> <m34:double> <m41:double> <m42:double> <m43:double> <m44:double>
498 *
499 * DOMQuad :-
500 * DOMQuadTag DOMQuadData
501 *
502 * DOMQuadData :-
503 * <p1:DOMPointData> <p2:DOMPointData> <p3:DOMPointData> <p4:DOMPointData>
504 *
505 */
506
507using DeserializationResult = std::pair<JSC::JSValue, SerializationReturnCode>;

509class CloneBase {
510protected:
511 CloneBase(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject)
512 : m_lexicalGlobalObject(lexicalGlobalObject)
513 , m_failed(false)
514 {
515 }
516
517 void fail()
518 {
519 m_failed = true;
520 }
521
522 JSGlobalObject* m_lexicalGlobalObject;

524 MarkedArgumentBuffer m_gcBuffer;

527#if ENABLE(WEB_CRYPTO)
528static bool wrapCryptoKey(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject, const Vector<uint8_t>& key, Vector<uint8_t>& wrappedKey)
529{
530 ScriptExecutionContext* scriptExecutionContext = scriptExecutionContextFromExecState(lexicalGlobalObject);
531 if (!scriptExecutionContext)
532 return false;
533 return scriptExecutionContext->wrapCryptoKey(key, wrappedKey);
534}
535
536static bool unwrapCryptoKey(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject, const Vector<uint8_t>& wrappedKey, Vector<uint8_t>& key)
537{
538 ScriptExecutionContext* scriptExecutionContext = scriptExecutionContextFromExecState(lexicalGlobalObject);
539 if (!scriptExecutionContext)
540 return false;
541 return scriptExecutionContext->unwrapCryptoKey(wrappedKey, key);
542}
543#endif
544
545#if ASSUME_LITTLE_ENDIAN
546template <typename T> static void writeLittleEndian(Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, T value)
547{
548 buffer.append(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&value), sizeof(value));
549}
550#else
551template <typename T> static void writeLittleEndian(Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, T value)
552{
553 for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(T); i++) {
554 buffer.append(value & 0xFF);
555 value >>= 8;
556 }
557}
558#endif
559
560template <> void writeLittleEndian<uint8_t>(Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, uint8_t value)
561{
562 buffer.append(value);
563}
564
565template <typename T> static bool writeLittleEndian(Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, const T* values, uint32_t length)
566{
567 if (length > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() / sizeof(T))
568 return false;
569
570#if ASSUME_LITTLE_ENDIAN
571 buffer.append(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(values), length * sizeof(T));
572#else
573 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; i++) {
574 T value = values[i];
575 for (unsigned j = 0; j < sizeof(T); j++) {
576 buffer.append(static_cast<uint8_t>(value & 0xFF));
577 value >>= 8;
578 }
579 }
580#endif
581 return true;
582}
583
584template <> bool writeLittleEndian<uint8_t>(Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, const uint8_t* values, uint32_t length)
585{
586 buffer.append(values, length);
587 return true;
588}

590class CloneSerializer : CloneBase {
591public:
592 static SerializationReturnCode serialize(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject, JSValue value, Vector<RefPtr<MessagePort>>& messagePorts, Vector<RefPtr<JSC::ArrayBuffer>>& arrayBuffers, const Vector<RefPtr<ImageBitmap>>& imageBitmaps,
593#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
594 const Vector<RefPtr<OffscreenCanvas>>& offscreenCanvases,
595#endif
596#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
597 const Vector<Ref<RTCDataChannel>>& rtcDataChannels,
598#endif
599#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
600 WasmModuleArray& wasmModules,
601 WasmMemoryHandleArray& wasmMemoryHandles,
602#endif
603 Vector<String>& blobURLs, Vector<uint8_t>& out, SerializationContext context, ArrayBufferContentsArray& sharedBuffers)
604 {
605 CloneSerializer serializer(lexicalGlobalObject, messagePorts, arrayBuffers, imageBitmaps,
606#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
607 offscreenCanvases,
608#endif
609#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
610 rtcDataChannels,
611#endif
612#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
613 wasmModules,
614 wasmMemoryHandles,
615#endif
616 blobURLs, out, context, sharedBuffers);
617 return serializer.serialize(value);
618 }
619
620 static bool serialize(StringView string, Vector<uint8_t>& out)
621 {
622 writeLittleEndian(out, CurrentVersion);
623 if (string.isEmpty()) {
624 writeLittleEndian<uint8_t>(out, EmptyStringTag);
625 return true;
626 }
627 writeLittleEndian<uint8_t>(out, StringTag);
628 if (string.is8Bit()) {
629 writeLittleEndian(out, string.length() | StringDataIs8BitFlag);
630 return writeLittleEndian(out, string.characters8(), string.length());
631 }
632 writeLittleEndian(out, string.length());
633 return writeLittleEndian(out, string.characters16(), string.length());
634 }
635
636private:
637 typedef HashMap<JSObject*, uint32_t> ObjectPool;
638
639 CloneSerializer(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject, Vector<RefPtr<MessagePort>>& messagePorts, Vector<RefPtr<JSC::ArrayBuffer>>& arrayBuffers, const Vector<RefPtr<ImageBitmap>>& imageBitmaps,
640#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
641 const Vector<RefPtr<OffscreenCanvas>>& offscreenCanvases,
642#endif
643#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
644 const Vector<Ref<RTCDataChannel>>& rtcDataChannels,
645#endif
646#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
647 WasmModuleArray& wasmModules,
648 WasmMemoryHandleArray& wasmMemoryHandles,
649#endif
650 Vector<String>& blobURLs, Vector<uint8_t>& out, SerializationContext context, ArrayBufferContentsArray& sharedBuffers)
651 : CloneBase(lexicalGlobalObject)
652 , m_buffer(out)
653 , m_blobURLs(blobURLs)
654 , m_emptyIdentifier(Identifier::fromString(lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), emptyString()))
655 , m_context(context)
656 , m_sharedBuffers(sharedBuffers)
657#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
658 , m_wasmModules(wasmModules)
659 , m_wasmMemoryHandles(wasmMemoryHandles)
660#endif
661 {
662 write(CurrentVersion);
663 fillTransferMap(messagePorts, m_transferredMessagePorts);
664 fillTransferMap(arrayBuffers, m_transferredArrayBuffers);
665 fillTransferMap(imageBitmaps, m_transferredImageBitmaps);
666#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
667 fillTransferMap(offscreenCanvases, m_transferredOffscreenCanvases);
668#endif
669#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
670 fillTransferMap(rtcDataChannels, m_transferredRTCDataChannels);
671#endif
672 }
673
674 template <class T>
675 void fillTransferMap(const Vector<RefPtr<T>>& input, ObjectPool& result)
676 {
677 if (input.isEmpty())
678 return;
679 JSDOMGlobalObject* globalObject = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(m_lexicalGlobalObject);
680 for (size_t i = 0; i < input.size(); i++) {
681 JSC::JSValue value = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, input[i].get());
682 JSC::JSObject* obj = value.getObject();
683 if (obj && !result.contains(obj))
684 result.add(obj, i);
685 }
686 }
687 template <class T>
688 void fillTransferMap(const Vector<Ref<T>>& input, ObjectPool& result)
689 {
690 if (input.isEmpty())
691 return;
692 JSDOMGlobalObject* globalObject = jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(m_lexicalGlobalObject);
693 for (size_t i = 0; i < input.size(); i++) {
694 JSC::JSValue value = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, input[i].get());
695 JSC::JSObject* obj = value.getObject();
696 if (obj && !result.contains(obj))
697 result.add(obj, i);
698 }
699 }

716 return object->inherits<JSMap>(vm);
717 }
718 bool isSet(VM& vm, JSValue value)
719 {

725
726 bool checkForDuplicate(JSObject* object)
727 {
728 // Record object for graph reconstruction
729 ObjectPool::const_iterator found = m_objectPool.find(object);
730
731 // Handle duplicate references
732 if (found != m_objectPool.end()) {
733 write(ObjectReferenceTag);
734 ASSERT(found->value < m_objectPool.size());
735 writeObjectIndex(found->value);
736 return true;
737 }
738
739 return false;
740 }
741
742 void recordObject(JSObject* object)
743 {
744 m_objectPool.add(object, m_objectPool.size());
745 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(object);
746 }
747
748 bool startObjectInternal(JSObject* object)
749 {
750 if (checkForDuplicate(object))
751 return false;
752 recordObject(object);
753 return true;
754 }
755
756 bool startObject(JSObject* object)
757 {
758 if (!startObjectInternal(object))
759 return false;
760 write(ObjectTag);
761 return true;
762 }

765 {
766 if (!startObjectInternal(array))
767 return false;
768
769 unsigned length = array->length();
770 write(ArrayTag);
771 write(length);
772 return true;
773 }
774
775 bool startSet(JSSet* set)

777 if (!startObjectInternal(set))
778 return false;
779
780 write(SetObjectTag);
781 return true;
782 }

784 bool startMap(JSMap* map)

798 JSValue getProperty(VM& vm, JSObject* object, const Identifier& propertyName)
799 {
800 PropertySlot slot(object, PropertySlot::InternalMethodType::Get);
801 if (object->methodTable(vm)->getOwnPropertySlot(object, m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyName, slot))
802 return slot.getValue(m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyName);
803 return JSValue();
804 }
805
806 void dumpImmediate(JSValue value, SerializationReturnCode& code)
807 {
808 if (value.isNull()) {
809 write(NullTag);
810 return;
811 }
812 if (value.isUndefined()) {
813 write(UndefinedTag);
814 return;
815 }
816 if (value.isNumber()) {
817 if (value.isInt32()) {
818 if (!value.asInt32())
819 write(ZeroTag);
820 else if (value.asInt32() == 1)
821 write(OneTag);
822 else {
823 write(IntTag);
824 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(value.asInt32()));
825 }
826 } else {
827 write(DoubleTag);
828 write(value.asDouble());
829 }
830 return;
831 }
832 if (value.isBoolean()) {
833 if (value.isTrue())
834 write(TrueTag);
835 else
836 write(FalseTag);
837 return;
838 }
839#if USE(BIGINT32)
840 if (value.isBigInt32()) {
841 write(BigIntTag);
842 dumpBigIntData(value);
843 return;
844 }
845#endif
846
847 // Make any new primitive extension safe by throwing an error.
848 code = SerializationReturnCode::DataCloneError;
849 }
850
851 void dumpString(const String& string)
852 {
853 if (string.isEmpty())
854 write(EmptyStringTag);
855 else {
856 write(StringTag);
857 write(string);
858 }
859 }
860
861 void dumpStringObject(const String& string)
862 {
863 if (string.isEmpty())
864 write(EmptyStringObjectTag);
865 else {
866 write(StringObjectTag);
867 write(string);
868 }
869 }
870
871 void dumpBigIntData(JSValue value)
872 {
873 ASSERT(value.isBigInt());
874#if USE(BIGINT32)
875 if (value.isBigInt32()) {
876 dumpBigInt32Data(value.bigInt32AsInt32());
877 return;
878 }
879#endif
880 dumpHeapBigIntData(jsCast<JSBigInt*>(value));
881 }
882
883#if USE(BIGINT32)
884 void dumpBigInt32Data(int32_t integer)
885 {
886 static_assert(sizeof(uint64_t) == sizeof(unsigned long long));
887 write(static_cast<uint8_t>(integer < 0));
888 if (!integer) {
889 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(0)); // Length-in-uint64_t
890 return;
891 }
892 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(1)); // Length-in-uint64_t
893 int64_t value = static_cast<int64_t>(integer);
894 if (value < 0)
895 value = -value;
896 write(static_cast<unsigned long long>(value));
897 }
898#endif
899
900 void dumpHeapBigIntData(JSBigInt* bigInt)
901 {
902 static_assert(sizeof(uint64_t) == sizeof(unsigned long long));
903 write(static_cast<uint8_t>(bigInt->sign()));
904 if constexpr (sizeof(JSBigInt::Digit) == sizeof(uint64_t)) {
905 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(bigInt->length()));
906 for (unsigned index = 0; index < bigInt->length(); ++index)
907 write(static_cast<unsigned long long>(bigInt->digit(index)));
908 } else {
909 ASSERT(sizeof(JSBigInt::Digit) == sizeof(uint32_t));
910 uint32_t lengthInUint64 = bigInt->length() / 2;
911 if (bigInt->length() & 0x1)
912 ++lengthInUint64;
913 write(lengthInUint64);
914 uint64_t value = 0;
915 for (unsigned index = 0; index < bigInt->length(); ++index) {
916 if (!(index & 0x1))
917 value = bigInt->digit(index);
918 else {
919 value = (static_cast<uint64_t>(bigInt->digit(index)) << 32) | value;
920 write(static_cast<unsigned long long>(value));
921 value = 0;
922 }
923 }
924 if (bigInt->length() & 0x1)
925 write(static_cast<unsigned long long>(value));
926 }
927 }

929 JSC::JSValue toJSArrayBuffer(ArrayBuffer& arrayBuffer)
930 {
931 auto& vm = m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm();
932 auto* globalObject = m_lexicalGlobalObject;
933 if (globalObject->inherits<JSDOMGlobalObject>(vm))
934 return toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, jsCast<JSDOMGlobalObject*>(globalObject), &arrayBuffer);
935
936 if (auto* buffer = arrayBuffer.m_wrapper.get())
937 return buffer;
938
939 return JSC::JSArrayBuffer::create(vm, globalObject->arrayBufferStructure(arrayBuffer.sharingMode()), &arrayBuffer);
940 }
941
942 bool dumpArrayBufferView(JSObject* obj, SerializationReturnCode& code)
943 {
944 VM& vm = m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm();
945 write(ArrayBufferViewTag);
946 if (obj->inherits<JSDataView>(vm))
947 write(DataViewTag);
948 else if (obj->inherits<JSUint8ClampedArray>(vm))
949 write(Uint8ClampedArrayTag);
950 else if (obj->inherits<JSInt8Array>(vm))
951 write(Int8ArrayTag);
952 else if (obj->inherits<JSUint8Array>(vm))
953 write(Uint8ArrayTag);
954 else if (obj->inherits<JSInt16Array>(vm))
955 write(Int16ArrayTag);
956 else if (obj->inherits<JSUint16Array>(vm))
957 write(Uint16ArrayTag);
958 else if (obj->inherits<JSInt32Array>(vm))
959 write(Int32ArrayTag);
960 else if (obj->inherits<JSUint32Array>(vm))
961 write(Uint32ArrayTag);
962 else if (obj->inherits<JSFloat32Array>(vm))
963 write(Float32ArrayTag);
964 else if (obj->inherits<JSFloat64Array>(vm))
965 write(Float64ArrayTag);
966 else if (obj->inherits<JSBigInt64Array>(vm))
967 write(BigInt64ArrayTag);
968 else if (obj->inherits<JSBigUint64Array>(vm))
969 write(BigUint64ArrayTag);
970 else
971 return false;
972
973 RefPtr<ArrayBufferView> arrayBufferView = toPossiblySharedArrayBufferView(vm, obj);
974 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(arrayBufferView->byteOffset()));
975 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(arrayBufferView->byteLength()));
976 RefPtr<ArrayBuffer> arrayBuffer = arrayBufferView->possiblySharedBuffer();
977 if (!arrayBuffer) {
978 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
979 return true;
980 }
981
982 return dumpIfTerminal(toJSArrayBuffer(*arrayBuffer), code);
983 }

1019 void dumpDOMMatrix(JSObject* obj)
1020 {
1021 VM& vm = m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm();
1022 if (obj->inherits<JSDOMMatrix>(vm))
1023 write(DOMMatrixTag);
1024 else
1025 write(DOMMatrixReadOnlyTag);
1026
1027 auto& matrix = jsCast<JSDOMMatrixReadOnly*>(obj)->wrapped();
1028 bool is2D = matrix.is2D();
1029 write(static_cast<uint8_t>(is2D));
1030 if (is2D) {
1031 write(matrix.m11());
1032 write(matrix.m12());
1033 write(matrix.m21());
1034 write(matrix.m22());
1035 write(matrix.m41());
1036 write(matrix.m42());
1037 } else {
1038 write(matrix.m11());
1039 write(matrix.m12());
1040 write(matrix.m13());
1041 write(matrix.m14());
1042 write(matrix.m21());
1043 write(matrix.m22());
1044 write(matrix.m23());
1045 write(matrix.m24());
1046 write(matrix.m31());
1047 write(matrix.m32());
1048 write(matrix.m33());
1049 write(matrix.m34());
1050 write(matrix.m41());
1051 write(matrix.m42());
1052 write(matrix.m43());
1053 write(matrix.m44());
1054 }
1055 }

1068 void dumpImageBitmap(JSObject* obj, SerializationReturnCode& code)
1069 {
1070 auto index = m_transferredImageBitmaps.find(obj);
1071 if (index != m_transferredImageBitmaps.end()) {
1072 write(ImageBitmapTransferTag);
1073 write(index->value);
1074 return;
1075 }
1076
1077 auto& imageBitmap = jsCast<JSImageBitmap*>(obj)->wrapped();
1078 auto* buffer = imageBitmap.buffer();
1079
1080 if (!buffer) {
1081 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
1082 return;
1083 }
1084
1085 PixelBufferFormat format { AlphaPremultiplication::Premultiplied, PixelFormat::RGBA8, DestinationColorSpace::SRGB() };
1086 const IntSize& logicalSize = buffer->logicalSize();
1087 auto pixelBuffer = buffer->getPixelBuffer(format, { IntPoint::zero(), logicalSize });
1088 if (!pixelBuffer) {
1089 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
1090 return;
1091 }
1092
1093 auto arrayBuffer = pixelBuffer->data().possiblySharedBuffer();
1094 if (!arrayBuffer) {
1095 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
1096 return;
1097 }
1098
1099 write(ImageBitmapTag);
1100 write(static_cast<uint8_t>(imageBitmap.serializationState().toRaw()));
1101 write(static_cast<int32_t>(logicalSize.width()));
1102 write(static_cast<int32_t>(logicalSize.height()));
1103 write(static_cast<double>(buffer->resolutionScale()));
1104
1105 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(arrayBuffer->byteLength()));
1106 write(static_cast<const uint8_t*>(arrayBuffer->data()), arrayBuffer->byteLength());
1107 }

1148
1149 bool dumpIfTerminal(JSValue value, SerializationReturnCode& code)
1150 {
1151 if (!value.isCell()) {
1152 dumpImmediate(value, code);
1153 return true;
1154 }
1155 ASSERT(value.isCell());
1156
1157 if (value.isString()) {
1158 dumpString(asString(value)->value(m_lexicalGlobalObject));
1159 return true;
1160 }
1161
1162 if (value.isHeapBigInt()) {
1163 write(BigIntTag);
1164 dumpBigIntData(value);
1165 return true;
1166 }
1167
1168 if (value.isSymbol()) {
1169 code = SerializationReturnCode::DataCloneError;
1170 return true;
1171 }
1172
1173 VM& vm = m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm();
1174 if (isArray(vm, value))
1175 return false;
1176
1177 if (value.isObject()) {
1178 auto* obj = asObject(value);
1179 if (auto* dateObject = jsDynamicCast<DateInstance*>(vm, obj)) {
1180 write(DateTag);
1181 write(dateObject->internalNumber());
1182 return true;
1183 }
1184 if (auto* booleanObject = jsDynamicCast<BooleanObject*>(vm, obj)) {
1185 if (!startObjectInternal(booleanObject)) // handle duplicates
1186 return true;
1187 write(booleanObject->internalValue().toBoolean(m_lexicalGlobalObject) ? TrueObjectTag : FalseObjectTag);
1188 return true;
1189 }
1190 if (auto* stringObject = jsDynamicCast<StringObject*>(vm, obj)) {
1191 if (!startObjectInternal(stringObject)) // handle duplicates
1192 return true;
1193 String str = asString(stringObject->internalValue())->value(m_lexicalGlobalObject);
1194 dumpStringObject(str);
1195 return true;
1196 }
1197 if (auto* numberObject = jsDynamicCast<NumberObject*>(vm, obj)) {
1198 if (!startObjectInternal(numberObject)) // handle duplicates
1199 return true;
1200 write(NumberObjectTag);
1201 write(numberObject->internalValue().asNumber());
1202 return true;
1203 }
1204 if (auto* bigIntObject = jsDynamicCast<BigIntObject*>(vm, obj)) {
1205 if (!startObjectInternal(bigIntObject)) // handle duplicates
1206 return true;
1207 JSValue bigIntValue = bigIntObject->internalValue();
1208 ASSERT(bigIntValue.isBigInt());
1209 write(BigIntObjectTag);
1210 dumpBigIntData(bigIntValue);
1211 return true;
1212 }
1213 if (auto* file = JSFile::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1214 write(FileTag);
1215 write(*file);
1216 return true;
1217 }
1218 if (auto* list = JSFileList::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1219 write(FileListTag);
1220 write(list->length());
1221 for (auto& file : list->files())
1222 write(file.get());
1223 return true;
1224 }
1225 if (auto* blob = JSBlob::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1226 write(BlobTag);
1227 m_blobURLs.append(blob->url().string());
1228 write(blob->url().string());
1229 write(blob->type());
1230 write(blob->size());
1231 return true;
1232 }
1233 if (auto* data = JSImageData::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1234 write(ImageDataTag);
1235 write(data->width());
1236 write(data->height());
1237 write(data->data().length());
1238 write(data->data().data(), data->data().length());
1239 write(data->colorSpace());
1240 return true;
1241 }
1242 if (auto* regExp = jsDynamicCast<RegExpObject*>(vm, obj)) {
1243 char flags[3];
1244 int flagCount = 0;
1245 if (regExp->regExp()->global())
1246 flags[flagCount++] = 'g';
1247 if (regExp->regExp()->ignoreCase())
1248 flags[flagCount++] = 'i';
1249 if (regExp->regExp()->multiline())
1250 flags[flagCount++] = 'm';
1251 write(RegExpTag);
1252 write(regExp->regExp()->pattern());
1253 write(String(flags, flagCount));
1254 return true;
1255 }
1256 if (obj->inherits<JSMessagePort>(vm)) {
1257 auto index = m_transferredMessagePorts.find(obj);
1258 if (index != m_transferredMessagePorts.end()) {
1259 write(MessagePortReferenceTag);
1260 write(index->value);
1261 return true;
1262 }
1263 // MessagePort object could not be found in transferred message ports
1264 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
1265 return true;
1266 }
1267 if (auto* arrayBuffer = toPossiblySharedArrayBuffer(vm, obj)) {
1268 if (arrayBuffer->isDetached()) {
1269 code = SerializationReturnCode::ValidationError;
1270 return true;
1271 }
1272 auto index = m_transferredArrayBuffers.find(obj);
1273 if (index != m_transferredArrayBuffers.end()) {
1274 write(ArrayBufferTransferTag);
1275 write(index->value);
1276 return true;
1277 }
1278 if (!startObjectInternal(obj)) // handle duplicates
1279 return true;
1280
1281 if (arrayBuffer->isShared() && m_context == SerializationContext::WorkerPostMessage) {
1282 uint32_t index = m_sharedBuffers.size();
1283 ArrayBufferContents contents;
1284 if (arrayBuffer->shareWith(contents)) {
1285 write(SharedArrayBufferTag);
1286 m_sharedBuffers.append(WTFMove(contents));
1287 write(index);
1288 return true;
1289 }
1290 }
1291
1292 write(ArrayBufferTag);
1293 write(arrayBuffer->byteLength());
1294 write(static_cast<const uint8_t*>(arrayBuffer->data()), arrayBuffer->byteLength());
1295 return true;
1296 }
1297 if (obj->inherits<JSArrayBufferView>(vm)) {
1298 if (checkForDuplicate(obj))
1299 return true;
1300 bool success = dumpArrayBufferView(obj, code);
1301 recordObject(obj);
1302 return success;
1303 }
1304#if ENABLE(WEB_CRYPTO)
1305 if (auto* key = JSCryptoKey::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1306 write(CryptoKeyTag);
1307 Vector<uint8_t> serializedKey;
1308 Vector<String> dummyBlobURLs;
1309 Vector<RefPtr<MessagePort>> dummyMessagePorts;
1310 Vector<RefPtr<JSC::ArrayBuffer>> dummyArrayBuffers;
1311#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
1312 WasmModuleArray dummyModules;
1313 WasmMemoryHandleArray dummyMemoryHandles;
1314#endif
1315 ArrayBufferContentsArray dummySharedBuffers;
1316 CloneSerializer rawKeySerializer(m_lexicalGlobalObject, dummyMessagePorts, dummyArrayBuffers, { },
1317#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
1318 { },
1319#endif
1320#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
1321 { },
1322#endif
1323#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
1324 dummyModules,
1325 dummyMemoryHandles,
1326#endif
1327 dummyBlobURLs, serializedKey, SerializationContext::Default, dummySharedBuffers);
1328 rawKeySerializer.write(key);
1329 Vector<uint8_t> wrappedKey;
1330 if (!wrapCryptoKey(m_lexicalGlobalObject, serializedKey, wrappedKey))
1331 return false;
1332 write(wrappedKey);
1333 return true;
1334 }
1335#endif
1336#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
1337 if (auto* rtcCertificate = JSRTCCertificate::toWrapped(vm, obj)) {
1338 write(RTCCertificateTag);
1339 write(rtcCertificate->expires());
1340 write(rtcCertificate->pemCertificate());
1341 write(rtcCertificate->origin().toString());
1342 write(rtcCertificate->pemPrivateKey());
1343 write(static_cast<unsigned>(rtcCertificate->getFingerprints().size()));
1344 for (const auto& fingerprint : rtcCertificate->getFingerprints()) {
1345 write(fingerprint.algorithm);
1346 write(fingerprint.value);
1347 }
1348 return true;
1349 }
1350#endif
1351#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
1352 if (JSWebAssemblyModule* module = jsDynamicCast<JSWebAssemblyModule*>(vm, obj)) {
1353 if (m_context != SerializationContext::WorkerPostMessage && m_context != SerializationContext::WindowPostMessage)
1354 return false;
1355
1356 uint32_t index = m_wasmModules.size();
1357 m_wasmModules.append(makeRef(module->module()));
1358 write(WasmModuleTag);
1359 write(index);
1360 return true;
1361 }
1362 if (JSWebAssemblyMemory* memory = jsDynamicCast<JSWebAssemblyMemory*>(vm, obj)) {
1363 if (memory->memory().sharingMode() != JSC::Wasm::MemorySharingMode::Shared) {
1364 code = SerializationReturnCode::DataCloneError;
1365 return true;
1366 }
1367 if (m_context != SerializationContext::WorkerPostMessage) {
1368 code = SerializationReturnCode::DataCloneError;
1369 return true;
1370 }
1371 uint32_t index = m_wasmMemoryHandles.size();
1372 m_wasmMemoryHandles.append(makeRef(memory->memory().handle()));
1373 write(WasmMemoryTag);
1374 write(index);
1375 return true;
1376 }
1377#endif
1378 if (obj->inherits<JSDOMPointReadOnly>(vm)) {
1379 dumpDOMPoint(obj);
1380 return true;
1381 }
1382 if (obj->inherits<JSDOMRectReadOnly>(vm)) {
1383 dumpDOMRect(obj);
1384 return true;
1385 }
1386 if (obj->inherits<JSDOMMatrixReadOnly>(vm)) {
1387 dumpDOMMatrix(obj);
1388 return true;
1389 }
1390 if (obj->inherits<JSDOMQuad>(vm)) {
1391 dumpDOMQuad(obj);
1392 return true;
1393 }
1394 if (obj->inherits(vm, JSImageBitmap::info())) {
1395 dumpImageBitmap(obj, code);
1396 return true;
1397 }
1398#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
1399 if (obj->inherits(vm, JSOffscreenCanvas::info())) {
1400 dumpOffscreenCanvas(obj, code);
1401 return true;
1402 }
1403#endif
1404#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
1405 if (obj->inherits(vm, JSRTCDataChannel::info())) {
1406 dumpRTCDataChannel(obj, code);
1407 return true;
1408 }
1409#endif
1410 if (obj->inherits(vm, JSDOMException::info())) {
1411 dumpDOMException(obj, code);
1412 return true;
1413 }
1414
1415 return false;
1416 }
1417 // Any other types are expected to serialize as null.
1418 write(NullTag);
1419 return true;
1420 }

1498
1499 template <class T> void writeConstantPoolIndex(const T& constantPool, unsigned i)
1500 {
1501 ASSERT(i < constantPool.size());
1502 if (constantPool.size() <= 0xFF)
1503 write(static_cast<uint8_t>(i));
1504 else if (constantPool.size() <= 0xFFFF)
1505 write(static_cast<uint16_t>(i));
1506 else
1507 write(static_cast<uint32_t>(i));
1508 }
1509
1510 void write(const Identifier& ident)
1511 {
1512 const String& str = ident.string();
1513 StringConstantPool::AddResult addResult = m_constantPool.add(ident.impl(), m_constantPool.size());
1514 if (!addResult.isNewEntry) {
1515 write(StringPoolTag);
1516 writeStringIndex(addResult.iterator->value);
1517 return;
1518 }
1519
1520 unsigned length = str.length();
1521
1522 // Guard against overflow
1523 if (length > (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() - sizeof(uint32_t)) / sizeof(UChar)) {
1524 fail();
1525 return;
1526 }
1527
1528 if (str.is8Bit())
1529 writeLittleEndian<uint32_t>(m_buffer, length | StringDataIs8BitFlag);
1530 else
1531 writeLittleEndian<uint32_t>(m_buffer, length);
1532
1533 if (!length)
1534 return;
1535 if (str.is8Bit()) {
1536 if (!writeLittleEndian(m_buffer, str.characters8(), length))
1537 fail();
1538 return;
1539 }
1540 if (!writeLittleEndian(m_buffer, str.characters16(), length))
1541 fail();
1542 }

1545 {
1546 if (str.isNull())
1547 write(m_emptyIdentifier);
1548 else
1549 write(Identifier::fromString(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), str));
1550 }

1557 }

1647 void write(CryptoKeyRSAComponents::Type type)
1648 {
1649 switch (type) {
1650 case CryptoKeyRSAComponents::Type::Public:
1651 write(CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Public);
1652 return;
1653 case CryptoKeyRSAComponents::Type::Private:
1654 write(CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Private);
1655 return;
1656 }

1658
1659 void write(const CryptoKeyRSAComponents& key)
1660 {
1661 write(key.type());
1662 write(key.modulus());
1663 write(key.exponent());
1664 if (key.type() == CryptoKeyRSAComponents::Type::Public)
1665 return;
1666
1667 write(key.privateExponent());
1668
1669 unsigned primeCount = key.hasAdditionalPrivateKeyParameters() ? key.otherPrimeInfos().size() + 2 : 0;
1670 write(primeCount);
1671 if (!primeCount)
1672 return;
1673
1674 write(key.firstPrimeInfo().primeFactor);
1675 write(key.firstPrimeInfo().factorCRTExponent);
1676 write(key.secondPrimeInfo().primeFactor);
1677 write(key.secondPrimeInfo().factorCRTExponent);
1678 write(key.secondPrimeInfo().factorCRTCoefficient);
1679 for (unsigned i = 2; i < primeCount; ++i) {
1680 write(key.otherPrimeInfos()[i].primeFactor);
1681 write(key.otherPrimeInfos()[i].factorCRTExponent);
1682 write(key.otherPrimeInfos()[i].factorCRTCoefficient);
1683 }
1684 }
1685
1686 void write(const CryptoKey* key)
1687 {
1688 write(currentKeyFormatVersion);
1689
1690 write(key->extractable());
1691
1692 CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages = key->usagesBitmap();
1693 write(countUsages(usages));
1694 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageEncrypt)
1695 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::Encrypt);
1696 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageDecrypt)
1697 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::Decrypt);
1698 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageSign)
1699 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::Sign);
1700 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageVerify)
1701 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::Verify);
1702 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageDeriveKey)
1703 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::DeriveKey);
1704 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageDeriveBits)
1705 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::DeriveBits);
1706 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageWrapKey)
1707 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::WrapKey);
1708 if (usages & CryptoKeyUsageUnwrapKey)
1709 write(CryptoKeyUsageTag::UnwrapKey);
1710
1711 switch (key->keyClass()) {
1712 case CryptoKeyClass::HMAC:
1713 write(CryptoKeyClassSubtag::HMAC);
1714 write(downcast<CryptoKeyHMAC>(*key).key());
1715 write(downcast<CryptoKeyHMAC>(*key).hashAlgorithmIdentifier());
1716 break;
1717 case CryptoKeyClass::AES:
1718 write(CryptoKeyClassSubtag::AES);
1719 write(key->algorithmIdentifier());
1720 write(downcast<CryptoKeyAES>(*key).key());
1721 break;
1722 case CryptoKeyClass::EC:
1723 write(CryptoKeyClassSubtag::EC);
1724 write(key->algorithmIdentifier());
1725 write(downcast<CryptoKeyEC>(*key).namedCurveString());
1726 switch (key->type()) {
1727 case CryptoKey::Type::Public: {
1728 write(CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Public);
1729 auto result = downcast<CryptoKeyEC>(*key).exportRaw();
1730 ASSERT(!result.hasException());
1731 write(result.releaseReturnValue());
1732 break;
1733 }
1734 case CryptoKey::Type::Private: {
1735 write(CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Private);
1736 // Use the standard complied method is not very efficient, but simple/reliable.
1737 auto result = downcast<CryptoKeyEC>(*key).exportPkcs8();
1738 ASSERT(!result.hasException());
1739 write(result.releaseReturnValue());
1740 break;
1741 }
1742 default:
1743 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1744 }
1745 break;
1746 case CryptoKeyClass::Raw:
1747 write(CryptoKeyClassSubtag::Raw);
1748 write(key->algorithmIdentifier());
1749 write(downcast<CryptoKeyRaw>(*key).key());
1750 break;
1751 case CryptoKeyClass::RSA:
1752 write(CryptoKeyClassSubtag::RSA);
1753 write(key->algorithmIdentifier());
1754 CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier hash;
1755 bool isRestrictedToHash = downcast<CryptoKeyRSA>(*key).isRestrictedToHash(hash);
1756 write(isRestrictedToHash);
1757 if (isRestrictedToHash)
1758 write(hash);
1759 write(*downcast<CryptoKeyRSA>(*key).exportData());
1760 break;
1761 }
1762 }
1763#endif
1764
1765 void write(const uint8_t* data, unsigned length)
1766 {
1767 m_buffer.append(data, length);
1768 }
1769
1770 Vector<uint8_t>& m_buffer;
1771 Vector<String>& m_blobURLs;
1772 ObjectPool m_objectPool;
1773 ObjectPool m_transferredMessagePorts;
1774 ObjectPool m_transferredArrayBuffers;
1775 ObjectPool m_transferredImageBitmaps;
1776#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
1777 ObjectPool m_transferredOffscreenCanvases;
1778#endif
1779#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
1780 ObjectPool m_transferredRTCDataChannels;
1781#endif
1782 typedef HashMap<RefPtr<UniquedStringImpl>, uint32_t, IdentifierRepHash> StringConstantPool;
1783 StringConstantPool m_constantPool;
1784 Identifier m_emptyIdentifier;
1785 SerializationContext m_context;
1786 ArrayBufferContentsArray& m_sharedBuffers;
1787#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
1788 WasmModuleArray& m_wasmModules;
1789 WasmMemoryHandleArray& m_wasmMemoryHandles;
1790#endif
1791};
1792
1793SerializationReturnCode CloneSerializer::serialize(JSValue in)
1794{
1795 VM& vm = m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm();
1796 Vector<uint32_t, 16> indexStack;
1797 Vector<uint32_t, 16> lengthStack;
1798 Vector<PropertyNameArray, 16> propertyStack;
1799 Vector<JSObject*, 32> inputObjectStack;
1800 Vector<JSMapIterator*, 4> mapIteratorStack;
1801 Vector<JSSetIterator*, 4> setIteratorStack;
1802 Vector<JSValue, 4> mapIteratorValueStack;
1803 Vector<WalkerState, 16> stateStack;
1804 WalkerState lexicalGlobalObject = StateUnknown;
1805 JSValue inValue = in;
1806 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
1807 while (1) {
1808 switch (lexicalGlobalObject) {
1809 arrayStartState:
1810 case ArrayStartState: {
1811 ASSERT(isArray(vm, inValue));
1812 if (inputObjectStack.size() > maximumFilterRecursion)
1813 return SerializationReturnCode::StackOverflowError;
1814
1815 JSArray* inArray = asArray(inValue);
1816 unsigned length = inArray->length();
1817 if (!startArray(inArray))
1818 break;
1819 inputObjectStack.append(inArray);
1820 indexStack.append(0);
1821 lengthStack.append(length);
1822 }
1823 arrayStartVisitMember:
1824 FALLTHROUGH;
1825 case ArrayStartVisitMember: {
1826 JSObject* array = inputObjectStack.last();
1827 uint32_t index = indexStack.last();
1828 if (index == lengthStack.last()) {
1829 indexStack.removeLast();
1830 lengthStack.removeLast();
1831
1832 propertyStack.append(PropertyNameArray(vm, PropertyNameMode::Strings, PrivateSymbolMode::Exclude));
1833 array->getOwnNonIndexPropertyNames(m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyStack.last(), DontEnumPropertiesMode::Exclude);
1834 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1835 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1836 if (propertyStack.last().size()) {
1837 write(NonIndexPropertiesTag);
1838 indexStack.append(0);
1839 goto objectStartVisitMember;
1840 }
1841 propertyStack.removeLast();
1842
1843 endObject();
1844 inputObjectStack.removeLast();
1845 break;
1846 }
1847 inValue = array->getDirectIndex(m_lexicalGlobalObject, index);
1848 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1849 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1850 if (!inValue) {
1851 indexStack.last()++;
1852 goto arrayStartVisitMember;
1853 }
1854
1855 write(index);
1856 auto terminalCode = SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted;
1857 if (dumpIfTerminal(inValue, terminalCode)) {
1858 if (terminalCode != SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted)
1859 return terminalCode;
1860 indexStack.last()++;
1861 goto arrayStartVisitMember;
1862 }
1863 stateStack.append(ArrayEndVisitMember);
1864 goto stateUnknown;
1865 }
1866 case ArrayEndVisitMember: {
1867 indexStack.last()++;
1868 goto arrayStartVisitMember;
1869 }
1870 objectStartState:
1871 case ObjectStartState: {
1872 ASSERT(inValue.isObject());
1873 if (inputObjectStack.size() > maximumFilterRecursion)
1874 return SerializationReturnCode::StackOverflowError;
1875 JSObject* inObject = asObject(inValue);
1876 if (!startObject(inObject))
1877 break;
1878 // At this point, all supported objects other than Object
1879 // objects have been handled. If we reach this point and
1880 // the input is not an Object object then we should throw
1881 // a DataCloneError.
1882 if (inObject->classInfo(vm) != JSFinalObject::info())
1883 return SerializationReturnCode::DataCloneError;
1884 inputObjectStack.append(inObject);
1885 indexStack.append(0);
1886 propertyStack.append(PropertyNameArray(vm, PropertyNameMode::Strings, PrivateSymbolMode::Exclude));
1887 inObject->methodTable(vm)->getOwnPropertyNames(inObject, m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyStack.last(), DontEnumPropertiesMode::Exclude);
1888 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1889 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1890 }
1891 objectStartVisitMember:
1892 FALLTHROUGH;
1893 case ObjectStartVisitMember: {
1894 JSObject* object = inputObjectStack.last();
1895 uint32_t index = indexStack.last();
1896 PropertyNameArray& properties = propertyStack.last();
1897 if (index == properties.size()) {
1898 endObject();
1899 inputObjectStack.removeLast();
1900 indexStack.removeLast();
1901 propertyStack.removeLast();
1902 break;
1903 }
1904 inValue = getProperty(vm, object, properties[index]);
1905 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1906 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1907
1908 if (!inValue) {
1909 // Property was removed during serialisation
1910 indexStack.last()++;
1911 goto objectStartVisitMember;
1912 }
1913 write(properties[index]);
1914
1915 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1916 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1917
1918 auto terminalCode = SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted;
1919 if (!dumpIfTerminal(inValue, terminalCode)) {
1920 stateStack.append(ObjectEndVisitMember);
1921 goto stateUnknown;
1922 }
1923 if (terminalCode != SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted)
1924 return terminalCode;
1925 FALLTHROUGH;
1926 }
1927 case ObjectEndVisitMember: {
1928 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1929 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1930
1931 indexStack.last()++;
1932 goto objectStartVisitMember;
1933 }
1934 mapStartState: {
1935 ASSERT(inValue.isObject());
1936 if (inputObjectStack.size() > maximumFilterRecursion)
1937 return SerializationReturnCode::StackOverflowError;
1938 JSMap* inMap = jsCast<JSMap*>(inValue);
1939 if (!startMap(inMap))
1940 break;
1941 JSMapIterator* iterator = JSMapIterator::create(vm, m_lexicalGlobalObject->mapIteratorStructure(), inMap, IterationKind::Entries);
1942 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(inMap);
1943 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(iterator);
1944 mapIteratorStack.append(iterator);
1945 inputObjectStack.append(inMap);
1946 goto mapDataStartVisitEntry;
1947 }
1948 mapDataStartVisitEntry:
1949 case MapDataStartVisitEntry: {
1950 JSMapIterator* iterator = mapIteratorStack.last();
1951 JSValue key, value;
1952 if (!iterator->nextKeyValue(m_lexicalGlobalObject, key, value)) {
1953 mapIteratorStack.removeLast();
1954 JSObject* object = inputObjectStack.last();
1955 ASSERT(jsDynamicCast<JSMap*>(vm, object));
1956 propertyStack.append(PropertyNameArray(vm, PropertyNameMode::Strings, PrivateSymbolMode::Exclude));
1957 object->methodTable(vm)->getOwnPropertyNames(object, m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyStack.last(), DontEnumPropertiesMode::Exclude);
1958 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
1959 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
1960 write(NonMapPropertiesTag);
1961 indexStack.append(0);
1962 goto objectStartVisitMember;
1963 }
1964 inValue = key;
1965 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(value);
1966 mapIteratorValueStack.append(value);
1967 stateStack.append(MapDataEndVisitKey);
1968 goto stateUnknown;
1969 }
1970 case MapDataEndVisitKey: {
1971 inValue = mapIteratorValueStack.last();
1972 mapIteratorValueStack.removeLast();
1973 stateStack.append(MapDataEndVisitValue);
1974 goto stateUnknown;
1975 }
1976 case MapDataEndVisitValue: {
1977 goto mapDataStartVisitEntry;
1978 }
1979
1980 setStartState: {
1981 ASSERT(inValue.isObject());
1982 if (inputObjectStack.size() > maximumFilterRecursion)
1983 return SerializationReturnCode::StackOverflowError;
1984 JSSet* inSet = jsCast<JSSet*>(inValue);
1985 if (!startSet(inSet))
1986 break;
1987 JSSetIterator* iterator = JSSetIterator::create(vm, m_lexicalGlobalObject->setIteratorStructure(), inSet, IterationKind::Keys);
1988 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(inSet);
1989 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(iterator);
1990 setIteratorStack.append(iterator);
1991 inputObjectStack.append(inSet);
1992 goto setDataStartVisitEntry;
1993 }
1994 setDataStartVisitEntry:
1995 case SetDataStartVisitEntry: {
1996 JSSetIterator* iterator = setIteratorStack.last();
1997 JSValue key;
1998 if (!iterator->next(m_lexicalGlobalObject, key)) {
1999 setIteratorStack.removeLast();
2000 JSObject* object = inputObjectStack.last();
2001 ASSERT(jsDynamicCast<JSSet*>(vm, object));
2002 propertyStack.append(PropertyNameArray(vm, PropertyNameMode::Strings, PrivateSymbolMode::Exclude));
2003 object->methodTable(vm)->getOwnPropertyNames(object, m_lexicalGlobalObject, propertyStack.last(), DontEnumPropertiesMode::Exclude);
2004 if (UNLIKELY(scope.exception()))
2005 return SerializationReturnCode::ExistingExceptionError;
2006 write(NonSetPropertiesTag);
2007 indexStack.append(0);
2008 goto objectStartVisitMember;
2009 }
2010 inValue = key;
2011 stateStack.append(SetDataEndVisitKey);
2012 goto stateUnknown;
2013 }
2014 case SetDataEndVisitKey: {
2015 goto setDataStartVisitEntry;
2016 }
2017
2018 stateUnknown:
2019 case StateUnknown: {
2020 auto terminalCode = SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted;
2021 if (dumpIfTerminal(inValue, terminalCode)) {
2022 if (terminalCode != SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted)
2023 return terminalCode;
2024 break;
2025 }
2026
2027 if (isArray(vm, inValue))
2028 goto arrayStartState;
2029 if (isMap(vm, inValue))
2030 goto mapStartState;
2031 if (isSet(vm, inValue))
2032 goto setStartState;
2033 goto objectStartState;
2034 }
2035 }
2036 if (stateStack.isEmpty())
2037 break;
2038
2039 lexicalGlobalObject = stateStack.last();
2040 stateStack.removeLast();
2041 }
2042 if (m_failed)
2043 return SerializationReturnCode::UnspecifiedError;
2044
2045 return SerializationReturnCode::SuccessfullyCompleted;
2046}
2047
2048class CloneDeserializer : CloneBase {
2049public:
2050 static String deserializeString(const Vector<uint8_t>& buffer)
2051 {
2052 if (buffer.isEmpty())
2053 return String();
2054 const uint8_t* ptr = buffer.begin();
2055 const uint8_t* end = buffer.end();
2056 uint32_t version;
2057 if (!readLittleEndian(ptr, end, version) || version > CurrentVersion)
2058 return String();
2059 uint8_t tag;
2060 if (!readLittleEndian(ptr, end, tag) || tag != StringTag)
2061 return String();
2062 uint32_t length;
2063 if (!readLittleEndian(ptr, end, length))
2064 return String();
2065 bool is8Bit = length & StringDataIs8BitFlag;
2066 length &= ~StringDataIs8BitFlag;
2067 String str;
2068 if (!readString(ptr, end, str, length, is8Bit))
2069 return String();
2070 return str;
2071 }
2072
2073 static DeserializationResult deserialize(JSGlobalObject* lexicalGlobalObject, JSGlobalObject* globalObject, const Vector<RefPtr<MessagePort>>& messagePorts, Vector<std::optional<ImageBitmapBacking>>&& backingStores
2074#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
2075 , Vector<std::unique_ptr<DetachedOffscreenCanvas>>&& detachedOffscreenCanvases
2076#endif
2077#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
2078 , Vector<std::unique_ptr<DetachedRTCDataChannel>>&& detachedRTCDataChannels
2079#endif
2080 , ArrayBufferContentsArray* arrayBufferContentsArray, const Vector<uint8_t>& buffer, const Vector<String>& blobURLs, const Vector<String> blobFilePaths, ArrayBufferContentsArray* sharedBuffers
2081#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
2082 , WasmModuleArray* wasmModules
2083 , WasmMemoryHandleArray* wasmMemoryHandles
2084#endif
2085 )
2086 {
2087 if (!buffer.size())
2088 return std::make_pair(jsNull(), SerializationReturnCode::UnspecifiedError);
2089 CloneDeserializer deserializer(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, messagePorts, arrayBufferContentsArray, buffer, blobURLs, blobFilePaths, sharedBuffers, WTFMove(backingStores)
2090#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS_IN_WORKERS)
2091 , WTFMove(detachedOffscreenCanvases)
2092#endif
2093#if ENABLE(WEB_RTC)
2094 , WTFMove(detachedRTCDataChannels)
2095#endif
2096#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
2097 , wasmModules
2098 , wasmMemoryHandles

2235 template <typename T> bool readLittleEndian(T& value)
2236 {
2237 if (m_failed || !readLittleEndian(m_ptr, m_end, value)) {
2238 fail();
2239 return false;
2240 }
2241 return true;
2242 }
2243#if ASSUME_LITTLE_ENDIAN
2244 template <typename T> static bool readLittleEndian(const uint8_t*& ptr, const uint8_t* end, T& value)
2245 {
2246 if (ptr > end - sizeof(value))
2247 return false;
2248
2249 if (sizeof(T) == 1)
2250 value = *ptr++;
2251 else {
2252 value = *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(ptr);
2253 ptr += sizeof(T);
2254 }
2255 return true;
2256 }
2257#else
2258 template <typename T> static bool readLittleEndian(const uint8_t*& ptr, const uint8_t* end, T& value)
2259 {
2260 if (ptr > end - sizeof(value))
2261 return false;
2262
2263 if (sizeof(T) == 1)
2264 value = *ptr++;
2265 else {
2266 value = 0;
2267 for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(T); i++)
2268 value += ((T)*ptr++) << (i * 8);
2269 }
2270 return true;
2271 }
2272#endif

2316 template <class T> bool readConstantPoolIndex(const T& constantPool, uint32_t& i)
2317 {
2318 if (constantPool.size() <= 0xFF) {
2319 uint8_t i8;
2320 if (!read(i8))
2321 return false;
2322 i = i8;
2323 return true;
2324 }
2325 if (constantPool.size() <= 0xFFFF) {
2326 uint16_t i16;
2327 if (!read(i16))
2328 return false;
2329 i = i16;
2330 return true;
2331 }
2332 return read(i);
2333 }
2334
2335 static bool readString(const uint8_t*& ptr, const uint8_t* end, String& str, unsigned length, bool is8Bit)
2336 {
2337 if (length >= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max() / sizeof(UChar))
2338 return false;
2339
2340 if (is8Bit) {
2341 if ((end - ptr) < static_cast<int>(length))
2342 return false;
2343 str = String { ptr, length };
2344 ptr += length;
2345 return true;
2346 }
2347
2348 unsigned size = length * sizeof(UChar);
2349 if ((end - ptr) < static_cast<int>(size))
2350 return false;
2351
2352#if ASSUME_LITTLE_ENDIAN
2353 str = String(reinterpret_cast<const UChar*>(ptr), length);
2354 ptr += length * sizeof(UChar);
2355#else
2356 Vector<UChar> buffer;
2357 buffer.reserveCapacity(length);
2358 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2359 uint16_t ch;
2360 readLittleEndian(ptr, end, ch);
2361 buffer.append(ch);
2362 }
2363 str = String::adopt(WTFMove(buffer));
2364#endif
2365 return true;
2366 }

2368 bool readStringData(CachedStringRef& cachedString)
2369 {
2370 bool scratch;
2371 return readStringData(cachedString, scratch);
2372 }
2373
2374 bool readStringData(CachedStringRef& cachedString, bool& wasTerminator)
2375 {
2376 if (m_failed)
2377 return false;
2378 uint32_t length = 0;
2379 if (!read(length))
2380 return false;
2381 if (length == TerminatorTag) {
2382 wasTerminator = true;
2383 return false;
2384 }
2385 if (length == StringPoolTag) {
2386 unsigned index = 0;
2387 if (!readStringIndex(index)) {
2388 fail();
2389 return false;
2390 }
2391 if (index >= m_constantPool.size()) {
2392 fail();
2393 return false;
2394 }
2395 cachedString = CachedStringRef(&m_constantPool, index);
2396 return true;
2397 }
2398 bool is8Bit = length & StringDataIs8BitFlag;
2399 length &= ~StringDataIs8BitFlag;
2400 String str;
2401 if (!readString(m_ptr, m_end, str, length, is8Bit)) {
2402 fail();
2403 return false;
2404 }
2405 m_constantPool.append(str);
2406 cachedString = CachedStringRef(&m_constantPool, m_constantPool.size() - 1);
2407 return true;
2408 }

2435 bool readFile(RefPtr<File>& file)
2436 {
2437 CachedStringRef path;
2438 if (!readStringData(path))
2439 return false;
2440 CachedStringRef url;
2441 if (!readStringData(url))
2442 return false;
2443 CachedStringRef type;
2444 if (!readStringData(type))
2445 return false;
2446 CachedStringRef name;
2447 if (!readStringData(name))
2448 return false;
2449 std::optional<int64_t> optionalLastModified;
2450 if (m_version > 6) {
2451 double lastModified;
2452 if (!read(lastModified))
2453 return false;
2454 if (lastModified >= 0)
2455 optionalLastModified = lastModified;
2456 }
2457
2458 // If the blob URL for this file has an associated blob file path, prefer that one over the "built-in" path.
2459 String filePath = blobFilePathForBlobURL(url->string());
2460 if (filePath.isEmpty())
2461 filePath = path->string();
2462
2463 if (!m_canCreateDOMObject)
2464 return true;
2465
2466 file = File::deserialize(scriptExecutionContextFromExecState(m_lexicalGlobalObject), filePath, URL(URL(), url->string()), type->string(), name->string(), optionalLastModified);
2467 return true;
2468 }

2484 bool readArrayBufferView(VM& vm, JSValue& arrayBufferView)
2485 {
2486 ArrayBufferViewSubtag arrayBufferViewSubtag;
2487 if (!readArrayBufferViewSubtag(arrayBufferViewSubtag))
2488 return false;
2489 uint32_t byteOffset;
2490 if (!read(byteOffset))
2491 return false;
2492 uint32_t byteLength;
2493 if (!read(byteLength))
2494 return false;
2495 JSObject* arrayBufferObj = asObject(readTerminal());
2496 if (!arrayBufferObj || !arrayBufferObj->inherits<JSArrayBuffer>(vm))
2497 return false;
2498
2499 unsigned elementSize = typedArrayElementSize(arrayBufferViewSubtag);
2500 if (!elementSize)
2501 return false;
2502 unsigned length = byteLength / elementSize;
2503 if (length * elementSize != byteLength)
2504 return false;
2505
2506 RefPtr<ArrayBuffer> arrayBuffer = toPossiblySharedArrayBuffer(vm, arrayBufferObj);
2507 switch (arrayBufferViewSubtag) {
2508 case DataViewTag:
2509 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, DataView::create(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2510 return true;
2511 case Int8ArrayTag:
2512 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Int8Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2513 return true;
2514 case Uint8ArrayTag:
2515 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Uint8Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2516 return true;
2517 case Uint8ClampedArrayTag:
2518 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Uint8ClampedArray::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2519 return true;
2520 case Int16ArrayTag:
2521 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Int16Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2522 return true;
2523 case Uint16ArrayTag:
2524 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Uint16Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2525 return true;
2526 case Int32ArrayTag:
2527 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Int32Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2528 return true;
2529 case Uint32ArrayTag:
2530 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Uint32Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2531 return true;
2532 case Float32ArrayTag:
2533 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Float32Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2534 return true;
2535 case Float64ArrayTag:
2536 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, Float64Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2537 return true;
2538 case BigInt64ArrayTag:
2539 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, BigInt64Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2540 return true;
2541 case BigUint64ArrayTag:
2542 arrayBufferView = toJS(m_lexicalGlobalObject, m_globalObject, BigUint64Array::tryCreate(WTFMove(arrayBuffer), byteOffset, length).get());
2543 return true;
2544 default:
2545 return false;
2546 }
2547 }

2710
2711 bool readRSAKey(bool extractable, CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages, RefPtr<CryptoKey>& result)
2712 {
2713 CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier algorithm;
2714 if (!read(algorithm))
2715 return false;
2716
2717 int32_t isRestrictedToHash;
2718 CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier hash = CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier::SHA_1;
2719 if (!read(isRestrictedToHash))
2720 return false;
2721 if (isRestrictedToHash && !read(hash))
2722 return false;
2723
2724 CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag type;
2725 if (!read(type))
2726 return false;
2727
2728 Vector<uint8_t> modulus;
2729 if (!read(modulus))
2730 return false;
2731 Vector<uint8_t> exponent;
2732 if (!read(exponent))
2733 return false;
2734
2735 if (type == CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Public) {
2736 auto keyData = CryptoKeyRSAComponents::createPublic(modulus, exponent);
2737 auto key = CryptoKeyRSA::create(algorithm, hash, isRestrictedToHash, *keyData, extractable, usages);
2738 result = WTFMove(key);
2739 return true;
2740 }
2741
2742 Vector<uint8_t> privateExponent;
2743 if (!read(privateExponent))
2744 return false;
2745
2746 uint32_t primeCount;
2747 if (!read(primeCount))
2748 return false;
2749
2750 if (!primeCount) {
2751 auto keyData = CryptoKeyRSAComponents::createPrivate(modulus, exponent, privateExponent);
2752 auto key = CryptoKeyRSA::create(algorithm, hash, isRestrictedToHash, *keyData, extractable, usages);
2753 result = WTFMove(key);
2754 return true;
2755 }
2756
2757 if (primeCount < 2)
2758 return false;
2759
2760 CryptoKeyRSAComponents::PrimeInfo firstPrimeInfo;
2761 CryptoKeyRSAComponents::PrimeInfo secondPrimeInfo;
2762 Vector<CryptoKeyRSAComponents::PrimeInfo> otherPrimeInfos(primeCount - 2);
2763
2764 if (!read(firstPrimeInfo.primeFactor))
2765 return false;
2766 if (!read(firstPrimeInfo.factorCRTExponent))
2767 return false;
2768 if (!read(secondPrimeInfo.primeFactor))
2769 return false;
2770 if (!read(secondPrimeInfo.factorCRTExponent))
2771 return false;
2772 if (!read(secondPrimeInfo.factorCRTCoefficient))
2773 return false;
2774 for (unsigned i = 2; i < primeCount; ++i) {
2775 if (!read(otherPrimeInfos[i].primeFactor))
2776 return false;
2777 if (!read(otherPrimeInfos[i].factorCRTExponent))
2778 return false;
2779 if (!read(otherPrimeInfos[i].factorCRTCoefficient))
2780 return false;
2781 }
2782
2783 auto keyData = CryptoKeyRSAComponents::createPrivateWithAdditionalData(modulus, exponent, privateExponent, firstPrimeInfo, secondPrimeInfo, otherPrimeInfos);
2784 auto key = CryptoKeyRSA::create(algorithm, hash, isRestrictedToHash, *keyData, extractable, usages);
2785 result = WTFMove(key);
2786 return true;
2787 }
2788
2789 bool readECKey(bool extractable, CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages, RefPtr<CryptoKey>& result)
2790 {
2791 CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier algorithm;
2792 if (!read(algorithm))
2793 return false;
2794 if (!CryptoKeyEC::isValidECAlgorithm(algorithm))
2795 return false;
2796 CachedStringRef curve;
2797 if (!readStringData(curve))
2798 return false;
2799 CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag type;
2800 if (!read(type))
2801 return false;
2802 Vector<uint8_t> keyData;
2803 if (!read(keyData))
2804 return false;
2805
2806 switch (type) {
2807 case CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Public:
2808 result = CryptoKeyEC::importRaw(algorithm, curve->string(), WTFMove(keyData), extractable, usages);
2809 break;
2810 case CryptoKeyAsymmetricTypeSubtag::Private:
2811 result = CryptoKeyEC::importPkcs8(algorithm, curve->string(), WTFMove(keyData), extractable, usages);
2812 break;
2813 }
2814
2815 return true;
2816 }

2818 bool readRawKey(CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages, RefPtr<CryptoKey>& result)
2819 {
2820 CryptoAlgorithmIdentifier algorithm;
2821 if (!read(algorithm))
2822 return false;
2823 Vector<uint8_t> keyData;
2824 if (!read(keyData))
2825 return false;
2826 result = CryptoKeyRaw::create(algorithm, WTFMove(keyData), usages);
2827 return true;
2828 }
2829
2830 bool readCryptoKey(JSValue& cryptoKey)
2831 {
2832 uint32_t keyFormatVersion;
2833 if (!read(keyFormatVersion) || keyFormatVersion > currentKeyFormatVersion)
2834 return false;
2835
2836 int32_t extractable;
2837 if (!read(extractable))
2838 return false;
2839
2840 uint32_t usagesCount;
2841 if (!read(usagesCount))
2842 return false;
2843
2844 CryptoKeyUsageBitmap usages = 0;
2845 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < usagesCount; ++i) {
2846 CryptoKeyUsageTag usage;
2847 if (!read(usage))
2848 return false;
2849 switch (usage) {
2850 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::Encrypt:
2851 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageEncrypt;
2852 break;
2853 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::Decrypt:
2854 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageDecrypt;
2855 break;
2856 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::Sign:
2857 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageSign;
2858 break;
2859 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::Verify:
2860 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageVerify;
2861 break;
2862 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::DeriveKey:
2863 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageDeriveKey;
2864 break;
2865 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::DeriveBits:
2866 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageDeriveBits;
2867 break;
2868 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::WrapKey:
2869 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageWrapKey;
2870 break;
2871 case CryptoKeyUsageTag::UnwrapKey:
2872 usages |= CryptoKeyUsageUnwrapKey;
2873 break;
2874 }
2875 }
2876
2877 CryptoKeyClassSubtag cryptoKeyClass;
2878 if (!read(cryptoKeyClass))
2879 return false;
2880 RefPtr<CryptoKey> result;
2881 switch (cryptoKeyClass) {
2882 case CryptoKeyClassSubtag::HMAC:
2883 if (!readHMACKey(extractable, usages, result))
2884 return false;
2885 break;
2886 case CryptoKeyClassSubtag::AES:
2887 if (!readAESKey(extractable, usages, result))
2888 return false;
2889 break;
2890 case CryptoKeyClassSubtag::RSA:
2891 if (!readRSAKey(extractable, usages, result))
2892 return false;
2893 break;
2894 case CryptoKeyClassSubtag::EC:
2895 if (!readECKey(extractable, usages, result))
2896 return false;
2897 break;
2898 case CryptoKeyClassSubtag::Raw:
2899 if (!readRawKey(usages, result))
2900 return false;
2901 break;
2902 }
2903 cryptoKey = getJSValue(result.get());
2904 return true;
2905 }

3215 JSValue readBigInt()
3216 {
3217 uint8_t sign = 0;
3218 if (!read(sign))
3219 return JSValue();
3220 uint32_t lengthInUint64 = 0;
3221 if (!read(lengthInUint64))
3222 return JSValue();
3223
3224 if (!lengthInUint64) {
3225#if USE(BIGINT32)
3226 return jsBigInt32(0);
3227#else
3228 JSBigInt* bigInt = JSBigInt::tryCreateZero(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm());
3229 if (UNLIKELY(!bigInt)) {
3230 fail();
3231 return JSValue();
3232 }
3233 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(bigInt);
3234 return bigInt;
3235#endif
3236 }
3237
3238#if USE(BIGINT32)
3239 static_assert(sizeof(JSBigInt::Digit) == sizeof(uint64_t));
3240 if (lengthInUint64 == 1) {
3241 static_assert(sizeof(unsigned long long) == sizeof(uint64_t));
3242 unsigned long long digit64 = 0;
3243 if (!read(digit64))
3244 return JSValue();
3245 if (sign) {
3246 if (digit64 <= static_cast<uint64_t>(-static_cast<int64_t>(INT32_MIN)))
3247 return jsBigInt32(static_cast<int32_t>(-static_cast<int64_t>(digit64)));
3248 } else {
3249 if (digit64 <= INT32_MAX)
3250 return jsBigInt32(static_cast<int32_t>(digit64));
3251 }
3252 ASSERT(digit64 != 0);
3253 JSBigInt* bigInt = JSBigInt::tryCreateWithLength(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), 1);
3254 if (!bigInt) {
3255 fail();
3256 return JSValue();
3257 }
3258 bigInt->setDigit(0, digit64);
3259 bigInt->setSign(sign);
3260 bigInt = bigInt->tryRightTrim(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm());
3261 if (!bigInt) {
3262 fail();
3263 return JSValue();
3264 }
3265 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(bigInt);
3266 return tryConvertToBigInt32(bigInt);
3267 }
3268#endif
3269 JSBigInt* bigInt = nullptr;
3270 if constexpr (sizeof(JSBigInt::Digit) == sizeof(uint64_t)) {
3271 bigInt = JSBigInt::tryCreateWithLength(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), lengthInUint64);
3272 if (!bigInt) {
3273 fail();
3274 return JSValue();
3275 }
3276 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < lengthInUint64; ++index) {
3277 static_assert(sizeof(unsigned long long) == sizeof(uint64_t));
3278 unsigned long long digit64 = 0;
3279 if (!read(digit64))
3280 return JSValue();
3281 bigInt->setDigit(index, digit64);
3282 }
3283 } else {
3284 ASSERT(sizeof(JSBigInt::Digit) == sizeof(uint32_t));
3285 bigInt = JSBigInt::tryCreateWithLength(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), lengthInUint64 * 2);
3286 if (!bigInt) {
3287 fail();
3288 return JSValue();
3289 }
3290 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < lengthInUint64; ++index) {
3291 static_assert(sizeof(unsigned long long) == sizeof(uint64_t));
3292 unsigned long long digit64 = 0;
3293 if (!read(digit64))
3294 return JSValue();
3295 bigInt->setDigit(index * 2, static_cast<uint32_t>(digit64));
3296 bigInt->setDigit(index * 2 + 1, static_cast<uint32_t>(digit64 >> 32));
3297 }
3298 }
3299 bigInt->setSign(sign);
3300 bigInt = bigInt->tryRightTrim(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm());
3301 if (!bigInt) {
3302 fail();
3303 return JSValue();
3304 }
3305 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(bigInt);
3306 return tryConvertToBigInt32(bigInt);

3309 JSValue readTerminal()
3310 {

3323 case ZeroTag:

3325 case OneTag:
3326 return jsNumber(1);
3327 case FalseTag:
3328 return jsBoolean(false);

3332 BooleanObject* obj = BooleanObject::create(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), m_globalObject->booleanObjectStructure());
3333 obj->setInternalValue(m_lexicalGlobalObject->vm(), jsBoolean(false));

3340 m_gcBuffer.appendWithCrashOnOverflow(obj);

3405 return JSValue();
3406 uint32_t length;

3408 return JSValue();
